ce:section.ce:para:
We compared the analytical parameters of Fe3+ and FA detection with previously reported papers. For Fe3+ ion detection, the analytical parameters are comparable to or better than most reported fluorescence analysis methods [43–46] (Table 1
                        ). In particular, Wu et al. also used hydrothermal to prepare fluorescent sulfur-doped carbon quantum dots with vitamin B1, and the detection limit and detection range for Fe3+ is 0.177 μM and 0.1–1.0 mM, respectively. For the detection of FA, although the detection limit is higher than the reported fluorescence methods [47–50], it has the advantage of a wide detection range. Therefore, we believe that the proposed analytical method using HCA-CDs as a fluorescent probe to detect Fe3+ and FA is a reliable method with high accuracy and selectivity. The comparison results show that the proposed method has better analysis parameters and practical application potential (Table 2
                        ).
